The author of this op-ed discusses the need for investment in the repair and maintenance of America's national parks. They emphasize that the parks are a representation of American values and heritage, and that they tell the story of the nation. The op-ed highlights the increasing number of visitors to the parks and the backlog of critical maintenance and repairs, which currently stands at $11.6 billion. The author commends the bipartisan bill before the Senate that aims to address this issue and recognizes the efforts of several senators involved in the process. They also thank President Trump for his proposed investment in public lands infrastructure. The op-ed concludes by stating that fixing and repairing the national park system is important for preserving an American institution for future generations.